18/04/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A NATO Parliamentary Assembly delegation kicked off a three-day visit to Macedonia on Sunday (17 April). Discussions are focusing on the pace of defence reforms, implementation of the Strategic Defence Review, and the process of transferring border control responsibilities from the army to the police. 
Also Sunday, Skopje marked the 60th anniversary of the establishment of the first Macedonian government. Addressing the public, Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski vowed that his cabinet would be the one to fulfil the strategic goals of NATO and EU accession. (Vecer, Makfax, Reuters - 18/04/05; Macedonian Government Web site, Makfax - 17/04/05)
